{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"text":"Colored Surface","type":"heading","anchor":"Colored-Surface","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" suffix (for instance "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"text":"How it works","type":"heading","anchor":"How-it-works","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"According to the color, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsUseMonochrome","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsOnColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"text":"How to use","type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-use","level":4},{"code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Debuging contrast ratios","type":"heading","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","level":5},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","isActive":true},{"text":", also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components like "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used on "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Divider","type":"heading","anchor":"Divider","level":3},{"text":"How it works","type":"heading","anchor":"How-it-works","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" To separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"OUDSVerticalDivider","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" To separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask).","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSDividerColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"How to use","type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-use","level":4},{"code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/